			<div class="about-artis">
				<div class="title">About the Artist</div>
				<div class="abt-content">
					<div class="con">
						<p>Mission Statement:</p>
						<p>A student of human behavior coupled with a desire to record everything he sees, Smith has been called the next artist to watch from Modern Art Magazine. The human
						experience is at the heart of what Smith is interested in and how people relate to each other.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="con">
						<p>Education:</p>
						<p>Smith studied at Parsons, NY for two years but is self taught otherwise. A full life experience from living on the street has propelled Smith to work with fascinating subjects
							such as soup kitchens, homeless people and the disparaged. Smith was invited to participate at Parsons through the recommendation of the director when he was
							discovered on the streets of New York painting in the subway and selling his work for $10.00 a painting. Smith is currently living in upstate New York in an artist colony
							and has been accepted full time at NYU’s art department.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="con">
						<p>Awards:</p>
						<p>Smith has received numerous awards including the prestigious National Youth Award and Artists to watch 2015.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			
